President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. and President Emmanuel Macron met at the G7 Summit and emphasized their commitment to strengthening bilateral ties and the Transatlantic alliance. They discussed their dedication to ending the COVID-19 pandemic by participating in the G7's vaccine donation initiative and improving global health security. They also expressed their commitment to reforming the international tax system to address inequalities caused by globalization. President Biden appreciated France's leadership on climate issues and both leaders emphasized their determination to achieve ambitious outcomes at the COP26 Summit in November. They also discussed efforts to enhance NATO, counter terrorism cooperation, and shared foreign policy priorities regarding China and Russia.